@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    BnSettingsPageRazor — Phase 7.1 Gate 1 TRANSITIONAL TWIN (design §"The
    method"): BnSettingsPage authored in .razor, mountable SIDE BY SIDE with
    the hand-written BnSettingsPage while RazorPageTwinTests proves their
    patch streams record-identical (mount + the Back navigation). At swap
    time this file is `git mv`ed to BnSettingsPage.razor (a .razor class is
    named by its FILE name), the .cs retires, and the twin test retires with
    it — the pre-existing goldens (NavigationTests, the shell suites) take
    over as the parity proof.

    Shape (the pinned mount contract — NavigationTests + the shells):
      BnView settings div                 backgroundColor+padding 16
       ├─ BnText title "Settings"        span, fontSize 24
       └─ BnButton "← Back"              button + click → NavigateToAsync("/")
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
<BnView BackgroundColor="@DefaultBackground" Padding="16">
    <BnText Text="Settings" FontSize="24" />
    <BnButton Label="← Back" OnClick="GoBack" />
</BnView>

@code {
    // BnDemo's DefaultBackground — the CascadingValue<BnTheme>-consistent look.
    private const string DefaultBackground = "#FFEEAA";

    /// <summary>The navigation service (Core contract) — same explicit
    /// [Inject] public property as the hand-written page (NOT @inject, which
    /// generates a private property: the public surface must not shrink in a
    /// conversion whose whole claim is "nothing changed").</summary>
    [Inject] public INavigationManager Navigation { get; set; } = default!;

    // Sync-completing (inline dispatcher): the swap has fully happened —
    // removes + creates delivered — when this Task is observed.
    private Task GoBack() => Navigation.NavigateToAsync("/").AsTask();
}
